header.gameNote: CHICAGO INVITATIONAL CHALLENGE AT HOFFMAN ESTATES IL

article.headline: Jackson St. 72-Savannah St. 71
article.story: HOFFMAN ESTATES, Ill. (AP) -- Jeremy Caldwell hit a jumper as time expired to give Jackson State a 72-71 victory over Savannah State on Friday in the Chicago Invitational Challenge. Joseph Flegler's 3 pointer gave Savannah State a 71-70 lead with 5.8 seconds left, but Jackson State and Caldwell answered with a jumper in the lane for the game winner. Trey Johnson led Jackson State (2-4) with 26 points and Caldwell finished with 12 points. Javon Randolph scored 29 points for Savannah State and Josh Obiajunwa finished with 12 points. Randolph scored 14 points in the first half for Savannah State (5-2), which shot 58 percent as a team. Johnson led Jackson State with 7 points in the first half.
